            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-12 09:27:10" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a chemical found in pale yellow mineral form; burns readily in air and is found in regions of vulcanic activity such as the Dead Sea area; causes land to be infertile; associated with punishment from God</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>sulfur</Gloss>
                <Gloss>brimstone</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In the NT θεῖον is always associated in some way with fire and refers to the kinds of burning hot rocks involved in volcanic eruptions. The closest equivalent in a number of languages is ‘burning stones’ or ‘fiery hot stones’ or ‘fiery red stones.’</Comments>
